  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ADMIN CUM ACCOUNTANT",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><ul><li><p>Handle full set of accounts including Accounts Payable (AP), Accounts Receivable (AR), General Ledger (GL), and bank reconciliations</p></li><li><p>Prepare monthly financial reports, management accounts, and cash flow statements</p></li><li><p>Assist in GST submission, corporate tax computation, and liaise with auditors, tax agents, and government authorities</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper accounting records, invoices, receipts, and supporting documents</p></li><li><p>Process payroll, CPF contributions, staff claims, and administrative payments</p></li><li><p>Support budgeting, expense tracking, and cost control activities</p></li><li><p>Perform general administrative duties including filing, documentation, and office coordination</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore accounting standards and company internal controls</p></li><li><p>Provide support for ad-hoc finance and administrative tasks as assigned</p></li></ul><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, or related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2–3 years of relevant accounting and administrative experience</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Singapore accounting practices, GST, CPF, and statutory requirements</p></li><li><p>Proficient in accounting software and Microsoft Excel</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail, organisational, and time-management skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and handle confidential information</p></li></ul>",
